g.aria-label: Obligations when enrolling at the DFH By enrolling at the German-French University, I commit myself to: • to take part in the entire course of study up to the final examinations provided for therein in accordance with the study and examination regulations agreed between all cooperation partners; • to study at the home, partner or third country university until obtaining the double degree and to complete all required examinations; • to re-register online with the DFH for each new academic year before September 30th of the current academic year. I acknowledge that if I do not meet this deadline, I will not be entitled to mobility allowance or the DFH certificate; • to prepare an experience report for each funding period in the form provided by the DFH as well as a final report at the end of the course of study; • For study programs offered by universities close to the border, I must present proof of residence to my home university showing that I actually live in the partner or third country. If I decide not to live in the partner or third country, I cannot receive the full mobility allowance. The reduced mobility allowance amounts to €150 per month; • to inform the program representative at my home university and the DFH within four weeks if I end or interrupt the DFH study program early. I acknowledge that if I discontinue the course of study, the mobility grants I have received to date can be reclaimed in whole or in part. The home university is eligible.

path.aria-label: I hereby confirm that I have taken note of the obligations by enrolling in the DFH
